The University of Dundee has been given a 5 Star rating by QS Quacquarelli Symonds, the international higher education specialists. QS Stars is a rating system that provides a detailed look at higher education institutions across the world, focusing on specific topics such as teaching strength, graduate employability, facilities, inclusiveness and innovation. Dundee achieved the 5 Star rating in all of the categories in which we have been assessed by QS over the last few months: Professor Wendy Alexander, Vice-Principal International, said, “The QS Stars rating system is a rigorous examination of data and performance and to gain 5 Stars is a notable achievement, emphasising the quality of our offering at Dundee. “This places us on the level of 5 Star universities around the world, and is testament to the work and quality of our staff and students here in Dundee.” For more on the QS Stars rating see https://www.topuniversities.com/universities/university-dundee If you would like to make enquiries about studying at the University of Dundee, please visit our website www.dundee.ac.uk or send an email to westafrica@dundee.ac.uk.